有些組織則對世界衛生組織的肥胖標準做了一些修正，比方說外科文獻上通常將「II級與III級肥胖」或只將「III級肥胖」打散重分如下，但細分的標準目前還沒有定論<ref name="morbid2007">{{Cite journal|title=Increases in morbid obesity in the USA: 2000–2005|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0033350607000121|last=Sturm|first=R.|date=2007-07|journal=Public Health|issue=7|doi=10.1016/j.puhe.2007.01.006|volume=121|pages=492–496|language=en|pmc=PMC2864630|pmid=17399752|access-date=2021-11-14|archive-date=2022-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220317023125/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0033350607000121|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
* BMI ≥ 35或40者為「嚴重肥胖」。
* BMI ≥ 35且患有肥胖相關健康問題者，或是BMI ≥ 40或45者為「病態肥胖」。
* BMI ≥ 45或50者為「極度肥胖」。

由於亞洲人相對於[[高加索人種|高加索人種]]而言，在較低的BMI就可能出現健康問題，因此部分國家和地区據此修正國內的肥胖定義。日本將BMI大於25定義為肥胖<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Criteria and classification of obesity in Japan and Asia-Oceania|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16145245/|last=Kanazawa|first=Masao|last2=Yoshiike|first2=Nobuo|date=2005|journal=World Review of Nutrition and Dietetics|doi=10.1159/000088200|volume=94|pages=1–12|issn=0084-2230|pmid=16145245|last3=Osaka|first3=Toshimasa|last4=Numba|first4=Yoshio|last5=Zimmet|first5=Paul|last6=Inoue|first6=Shuji|access-date=2021-11-14|archive-date=2022-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312143224/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16145245/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；中國大陸為大於28<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Predictive values of body mass index and waist circumference for risk factors of certain related diseases in Chinese adults--study on optimal cut-off points of body mass index and waist circumference in Chinese adults|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12046553/|last=Zhou|first=Bei-Fan|last2=Cooperative Meta-Analysis Group of the Working Group on Obesity in China|date=2002-03|journal=Biomedical and environmental sciences: BES|issue=1|doi=10.1046/j.1440-6047.11.s8.9.x|volume=15|pages=83–96|issn=0895-3988|pmid=12046553|access-date=2021-11-14|archive-date=2021-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211210200017/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12046553/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；台灣則為大於27<ref>{{cite web |url=http://obesity.hpa.gov.tw/TC/downloadList.aspx?cid=82 |title=國民健康署肥胖防治網成人健康體重對照表 |publisher=Obesity.hpa.gov.tw |date=2015-12-17 |accessdate=2016-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126160947/http://obesity.hpa.gov.tw/TC/downloadList.aspx?cid=82 |archive-date=2016-01-26 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

===其他判斷肥胖的方式===
[[腰臀比|腰臀比]]也是一種用來判斷肥胖的標準，根據世衛組織的定義，男性大於 0.9m 或女性大於 0.85m 即屬肥胖<ref name=WHO2008>{{cite web|url=http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2011/9789241501491_eng.pdf|title=Waist Circumference and Waist-Hip Ratio|work=World Health Organization|accessdate=2016-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209033722/http://whqlibdoc.who.int/publications/2011/9789241501491_eng.pdf|archive-date=2015-02-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>。<BR>有研究指出，腰臀比能比BMI更準確地預測心血管疾病風險<ref name="MørkedalRomundstad2011">{{Cite journal|title=Informativeness of indices of blood pressure, obesity and serum lipids in relation to ischaemic heart disease mortality: the HUNT-II study|url=http://link.springer.com/10.1007/s10654-011-9572-7|last=Mørkedal|first=Bjørn|last2=Romundstad|first2=Pål R|date=2011-06|journal=European Journal of Epidemiology|issue=6|doi=10.1007/s10654-011-9572-7|volume=26|pages=457–461|language=en|issn=0393-2990|pmc=PMC3115050|pmid=21461943|last3=Vatten|first3=Lars J.}}</ref>；且相較於腰圍或BMI，腰臀比和老人（大於75歲）的死亡率關係更為密切<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Weight, shape, and mortality risk in older persons: elevated waist-hip ratio, not high body mass index, is associated with a greater risk of death|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16895897|last=Price|first=Gill M.|last2=Uauy|first2=Ricardo|date=2006-08|journal=The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition|issue=2|doi=10.1093/ajcn/84.1.449|volume=84|pages=449–460|issn=0002-9165|pmid=16895897|last3=Breeze|first3=Elizabeth|last4=Bulpitt|first4=Christopher J.|last5=Fletcher|first5=Astrid E.|access-date=2021-11-14|archive-date=2022-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121140747/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16895897/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

