===生存矛盾===
雖然有大量證據支持一般人的肥胖會對健康造成負面影響，但在部分族群中BMI的上升卻似乎對健康有幫助。這個現象稱為「肥胖生存矛盾」<ref name=Schmidt2007>{{cite journal | author = Schmidt DS, Salahudeen AK | title = Obesity-survival paradox-still a controversy? | journal = Semin Dial | volume = 20 | issue = 6 | pages = 486–92 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17991192 | doi = 10.1111/j.1525-139X.2007.00349.x | type = Review }}</ref>，1999年時，此現象首次在過重與肥胖的[[血液透析|血液透析]]患者身上發現<ref name=Schmidt2007/>，稍後也在[[心衰竭|心衰竭]]與[[周邊血管疾病|周邊血管疾病]]的患者身上發現<ref name=paradox2003>{{cite journal | author = U.S. Preventive Services Task Force | title = Behavioral counseling in primary care to promote a healthy diet: recommendations and rationale | journal = Am Fam Physician | volume = 67 | issue = 12 | pages = 2573–6 | date = 2003-06 | pmid = 12825847 | doi = | type = Review }}</ref>。

對於患有[[心衰竭|心衰竭]]的人而言，BMI界於30.0-34.9間的人死亡率比正常體重者來得低，心衰竭患者在病情惡化時伴隨的體重減輕或許能解釋此一現象<ref>{{cite journal | author = Habbu A, Lakkis NM, Dokainish H | title = The obesity paradox: Fact or fiction? | journal = Am. J. Cardiol. | volume = 98 | issue = 7 | pages = 944–8 | date = 2006-10 | pmid = 16996880 | doi = 10.1016/j.amjcard.2006.04.039 | type = Review }}</ref>，其他的心臟疾病也能發現類似的情形。一級肥胖的心臟病患者在未來發生其他心臟問題的機會，並不會比體重正常的心臟病患者來得高；但對於肥胖程度更高的患者來說，未來發生其他心血管問題的機會就會開始上升<ref>{{cite journal | author = Romero-Corral A, Montori VM, Somers VK, Korinek J, Thomas RJ, Allison TG, Mookadam F, Lopez-Jimenez F | title = Association of bodyweight with total mortality and with cardiovascular events in coronary artery disease: A systematic review of cohort studies | journal = Lancet | volume = 368 | issue = 9536 | pages = 666–78 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16920472 | doi = 10.1016/S0140-6736(06)69251-9 | type = Review }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | author = Oreopoulos A, Padwal R, Kalantar-Zadeh K, Fonarow GC, Norris CM, McAlister FA | title = Body mass index and mortality in heart failure: A meta-analysis | journal = Am. Heart J. | volume = 156 | issue = 1 | pages = 13–22 | date = 2008-07 | pmid = 18585492 | doi = 10.1016/j.ahj.2008.02.014 | url = | type = Meta-analysis, Review }}</ref>。即使對接受[[心血管繞道手術|心血管繞道手術]]的患者而言，肥胖與過重的患者死亡率相對於一般人也沒有上升<ref>{{cite journal | author = Oreopoulos A, Padwal R, Norris CM, Mullen JC, Pretorius V, Kalantar-Zadeh K | title = Effect of obesity on short- and long-term mortality postcoronary revascularization: A meta-analysis | journal = Obesity (Silver Spring) | volume = 16 | issue = 2 | pages = 442–50 | date = 2008-02 | pmid = 18239657 | doi = 10.1038/oby.2007.36 | type = Meta-analysis }}</ref>。研究指出，肥胖與過重的患者預後較預期良好是由於它們在心臟病發作後會得到較積極的治療<ref>{{cite journal | author = Diercks DB, Roe MT, Mulgund J, Pollack CV, Kirk JD, Gibler WB, Ohman EM, Smith SC, Boden WE, Peterson ED | title = The obesity paradox in non-ST-segment elevation acute coronary syndromes: Results from the Can Rapid risk stratification of Unstable angina patients Suppress ADverse outcomes with Early implementation of the American College of Cardiology/American Heart Association Guidelines Quality Improvement Initiative | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-heart-journal_2006-07_152_1/page/140 | journal = Am Heart J | volume = 152 | issue = 1 | pages = 140–8 | date = 2006-07 | pmid = 16824844 | doi = 10.1016/j.ahj.2005.09.024 | type = Research Support }}</ref>，也有研究指出若[[周邊血管疾病|周邊血管疾病]]患者同時又患有[[慢性阻塞性肺病|慢性阻塞性肺病]]，那肥胖對預後的改善就不復存在<ref name=paradox2003/>。

== 肥胖症的病因 ==
大多数的学者认为过多的能量摄入和坐式生活方式是导致肥胖症的主要原因。<ref>{{cite book | author=Sara Bleich, David Cutler, Christopher Murray, Alyce Adams | title=Working paper 12954: Why is the developed world obese? | publisher=National Bureau of Economic Research | date=2007-03 | url=http://www.nber.org/papers/w12954 | access-date=2008-12-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114172725/http://www.nber.org/papers/w12954 | archive-date=2009-01-14 | dead-url=no }}</ref>少数情况下，食物过量摄入与遗传、生理和心理疾病有关，<ref name=Pool2001>{{cite book |author=Pool, Robert |title=Fat: Fighting the Obesity Epidemic |url=https://archive.org/details/fatfightingobesi00pool |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Oxford, UK |year=2001 |pages= |isbn=0-19-511853-7}}</ref>当然也有部分原因來自文化差异和工業化大量生产。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Nestle M, Jacobson MF |title=Halting the obesity epidemic: A public health policy approach |journal=Public Health Rep |volume=115 |issue=1 |pages=12–24 |year=2000 |pmid=10968581 |pmc=1308552 |doi= 10.1093/phr/115.1.12|url=}}</ref><ref name=James2008/>

就個人層面來說，[[食物熱量|熱量]]攝取過多與[[體能鍛煉|運動]]不足可以解釋大多數肥胖者的發胖<ref name="CADG2006">{{cite journal|title=2006 Canadian clinical practice guidelines on the management and prevention of obesity in adults and children summary|author=Lau DC, Douketis JD, Morrison KM, Hramiak IM, Sharma AM, Ur E|url=http://www.cmaj.ca/cgi/content/full/176/8/S1|date=2007-04|journal=CMAJ|issue=8|doi=10.1503/cmaj.061409|volume=176|pages=S1–13|type=Practice Guideline, Review|pmc=1839777|pmid=17420481|access-date=2016-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610222726/http://www.cmaj.ca/cgi/content/full/176/8/S1|archive-date=2011-06-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但仍有一小部分肥胖者是基因、醫療、或精神疾病所造成的<ref>{{cite journal | author = Bleich S, Cutler D, Murray C, Adams A | title = Why is the developed world obese? | journal = Annu Rev Public Health | volume = 29 | pages = 273–95 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18173389 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.publhealth.29.020907.090954 | type = Research Support }}</ref>。另一方面，社群中整體肥胖率的上升則歸因於食物取得變得容易、食物變得更為可口<ref>{{cite journal | author = Drewnowski A, Specter SE | title = Poverty and obesity: the role of energy density and energy costs | journal = Am. J. Clin. Nutr. | volume = 79 | issue = 1 | pages = 6–16 | date = 2004-01 | pmid = 14684391 | doi =  | url = http://www.ajcn.org/cgi/content/full/79/1/6 | type = Review | access-date = 2016-01-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100613170937/http://www.ajcn.org/cgi/content/full/79/1/6 | archive-date = 2010-06-13 | dead-url = no }}</ref>、以及車輛與機械化生產的普及<ref>{{cite journal | author = Nestle M, Jacobson MF | title = Halting the obesity epidemic: a public health policy approach | journal = Public Health Rep | volume = 115 | issue = 1 | pages = 12–24 | year = 2000 | pmid = 10968581 | pmc = 1308552 | doi = 10.1093/phr/115.1.12 | url = | type = Research Support }}</ref><ref name=James2008>{{cite journal | author = James WP | title = The fundamental drivers of the obesity epidemic | journal = Obes Rev | volume = 9 | issue = Suppl 1 | pages = 6–13 | date = 2008-03 | pmid = 18307693 | doi = 10.1111/j.1467-789X.2007.00432.x | type = Review }}</ref>。

2006年发表的一篇综述总结了10种导致肥胖症[[发病率|发病率]]和[[患病率|患病率]]增高的其他原因：
# [[睡眠|睡眠]]不足
# [[激素样活性物质|内分泌干扰物]]（能影响[[脂肪酸代谢|脂肪酸代谢]]的環境汙染物）
# 生活環境的溫度變化率下降
# 吸菸率下降（吸菸會抑制食慾）
# 造成體重上升的藥物使用率增加（例如第二代[[抗精神病藥|抗精神病藥]]）
# 人口組成的改變（平均體重較高的年齡層或種族佔的比例增加）
# 懷孕年齡的延後（可能造成兒童更容易肥胖）
# 促使發胖的[[表徵遺傳學|表徵遺傳]]因子隨世代累積
# BMI高的人在[[自然选择|自然选择]]过程中具有一定的优势
# [[选择性配对|选择性配对]]，相同体重等级的人容易相互认识（這會使肥胖與消瘦的人數都上升，整體的體重變異數也會上升）<ref name="pmid16801930">{{cite journal |author=Keith SW, Redden DT, Katzmarzyk PT, ''et al.'' |title=Putative contributors to the secular increase in obesity: Exploring the roads less traveled |journal=Int J Obes (Lond) |volume=30 |issue=11 |pages=1585–94 |year=2006 |pmid=16801930 |doi=10.1038/sj.ijo.0803326 |url=http://www.nature.com/ijo/journal/v30/n11/full/0803326a.html |access-date=2008-12-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120044951/http://www.nature.com/ijo/journal/v30/n11/full/0803326a.html |archive-date=2017-01-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

雖然有許多證據支持這些原因在肥胖發生過程中扮演的角色，但目前仍缺乏決定性的證據斷言它們和肥胖症的關聯，而作者也認為這些原因對肥胖的影響可能也小於上段所談的其他因素<ref name="pmid16801930"/>。

